                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115R39/35</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-16T20:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1917—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>180. Department’s 177, May 12, 7 p.m. Foreign Office states that inasmuch as
                    proceedings had been begun in the Richardson case no further suspension could be
                    obtained but nevertheless suspension has been granted in case of Stocker and
                    other owners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
